    "causal_summary": "A 10-lineage parallel audit (round-2 re-verified: 73 confirmed, 0 false positives, +75 new) found the `/doctor` command router, its per-target assets, the three subsystem install guides, and the subsystem READMEs are **not** aligned with current reality. The drift is systemic across nine clusters: a code-graph DB-path that moved skill-local (2026-05-29) but is still documented at the old shared location; doctor-router mutation classes that promise apply/rebuild behavior the read-only `doctor.sh` scripts do not implement; tool-count/version drift (35→36 tools, Node 18→20.11, phantom v1.8.1, \"6 servers\"→5); incomplete colon-form `/doctor:*` deprecation; install guides that launch the backend directly instead of the front-proxy launcher; a Python `sentence-transformers` sidecar that is now pure-Node hf-local; stale tool lists with invalid MCP-call examples; wrong rebuild targets; and skill-advisor lane-id drift (`semantic_shadow` now live, not shadow-only).",
